review_blob: Very beautiful golden red color -- not typical of hefeweizens by other brewers. One of my favorite hefeweizens though! Best to try it cold, from the tap at the brewery tasting room. Still good from the bottle, though.

Palate: light body, soft carbonation, thin feel .
Flavor: medium sweetness, lightly bitter, lightly sour, paper napkin. 
Aroma: bread, grass. 
Appearance: pale, clear, sparkling, white foam.
The typical "cheap keg beer" at parties. Good for drinking games, light flavor, easy to drink.
